1Ô∏è‚É£ Monitoring Gateway Load Balancer
üîπ CloudWatch Integration

Elastic Load Balancing publishes metrics to Amazon CloudWatch

Metrics are available for:

Gateway Load Balancer

Registered targets (virtual appliances)

Metrics are stored as time-series data

Each metric has:

Timestamp

Optional unit

üìå Exam Point:
CloudWatch is the primary monitoring service for GWLB.

2Ô∏è‚É£ When Are Metrics Published?

Metrics are published ONLY when traffic is flowing

Metrics interval: every 60 seconds

‚ùå If no traffic, no metrics are reported

üìå This is commonly tested in exam scenarios.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Important GWLB CloudWatch Metrics (VERY IMPORTANT)
‚úÖ ActiveFlowCount

Total number of concurrent active flows

Indicates current traffic load

‚úÖ NewFlowCount

Number of new connections/flows created in a time period

‚úÖ HealthyHostCount

Number of healthy virtual appliance targets

‚úÖ UnHealthyHostCount

Number of unhealthy targets

Helps detect appliance failures

‚úÖ ProcessedBytes

Total bytes processed by GWLB

Includes:

Incoming traffic

Outgoing traffic

‚ùå Does NOT include health check traffic

‚úÖ ConsumedLCUs

Number of Load Balancer Capacity Units (LCUs) used

Directly impacts billing

4Ô∏è‚É£ What Is a Gateway Load Balancer Capacity Unit (GLCU)?

GLCU is used to measure capacity usage

Based on:

New flows per second

Active flows

Processed bytes

Example (Exam Style)

100 new connections/sec

Each lasting 4 minutes

‚âà 24,000 active connections

‚âà 0.4 GLCU

5Ô∏è‚É£ GWLB Pricing Model (High-Level)
üí∞ You Pay For:

GWLB running hours

GLCU usage per hour

üìå Pricing varies by region.

üîπ Example (Mumbai Region ‚Äì Illustration)

~$0.01 per GWLB hour

~$0 per GLCU hour (example only)

Always check AWS pricing page for exact rates

6Ô∏è‚É£ Free Tier

750 GWLB hours per month

Applies under AWS Free Tier

GLCU usage may still apply beyond limits

7Ô∏è‚É£ Cost Optimization Tips (Exam Perspective)

Reduce:

Unnecessary traffic

Idle appliances

Use:

Auto Scaling Groups

Health checks

Monitor:

ActiveFlowCount

ConsumedLCUs

8Ô∏è‚É£ One-Line Exam Summary

Gateway Load Balancer monitoring is done using CloudWatch metrics published every 60 seconds only when traffic flows, and pricing is based on running hours and GLCU consumption.

